provisions.content:
_ In this Act unless the context otherwise requires,
(a)     “Administration” means administration of Daanish School comprising a principal,
senior teacher, teachers and other staff etc.;
(b)     “Authority” means the Daanish Schools Authority established under section 3;
(c)     “Chairperson” means the Prime Minister of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan or a
person of eminence nominated by him;
(d)     “destitute child” means a child whose combined household's gross income does
not exceed the minimum wage as notified by the Federal Government or any other
amount specified by the Authority;
(e)     “Vice-Chairperson” means the Federal Minister of the Division concerned;
(f)     “Daanish School” means a School established or notified by the Authority under
this Act and includes any school established or notified before the commencement
of this Act;
(g)     “Executive Committee” means a committee constituted under section 7;
(h)     “Fund” means the Fund established under section 13;
(i)     “governing body” means governing body constituted under section 9;
(j)     “Government” means Federal Government;
(k)     “member” means a member of the Authority;
(l)     “Managing Director” means Managing Director of the Authority appointed under
section 6;
(m)     “prescribed” means prescribed by rules or regulations made under this Act;
(n)     “rules” means rules made under this Act;
(o)     “regulations” means regulations made under this Act;
(p)     “student” means a student of a Daanish School; and
(q)     “teacher” includes the Principal and an employee of a Daanish School who is
imparting instructions to the students.
